"title": "4269: Sinai, Mount",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4269",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The mountain in the Sinai peninsula (probably present-day Jebel Musa), also called Horeb in the OT, where God made a covenant with Israel, establishing them as his people and giving them his laws. In the NT Sinai is seen as symbolising the old covenant.</p>\n<h2>Mount Sinai and the call of Moses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1-Exod3:10\">EXO 3:1–3:10</a></strong> <em>Most scholars agree that the names Horeb and Sinai are used interchangeably of the same mountain, although some see them as referring to separate peaks within the same range.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:30-Acts7:34\">ACT 7:30–7:34</a></p>\n<h2>God reveals himself to Israel at Mount Sinai</h2>\n<h3>The people of Israel arrive at Mount Sinai three months after leaving Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:1-Exod19:2\">EXO 19:1–19:2</a></p>\n<h3>God promises to make Israel his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:3-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:3–19:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God calls for holiness among his people</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10-Exod19:15\">EXO 19:10–19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:20-Exod19:24\">EXO 19:20–19:24</a></p>\n<h3>God appears in a theophany</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:19\">EXO 19:16–19:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:10-Deut4:12\">DEU 4:10–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:18-Heb12:21\">HEB 12:18–12:21</a></p>\n<h2>God gives his laws to Israel on Mount Sinai</h2>\n<h3>God gives Israel the Ten Commandments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:1-Exod20:17\">EXO 20:1–20:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:21\">DEU 5:6–5:21</a></p>\n<h3>Israel responds with fear to God's revelation</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:18-Exod20:21\">EXO 20:18–20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:23-Deut5:27\">DEU 5:23–5:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:16\">DEU 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>God gives Israel the Book of the Covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:22-Exod23:19\">EXO 20:22–23:19</a> <em>These laws, largely an expansion and exposition of the Ten Commandments, are called “the Book of the Covenant” in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:7\">Ex 24:7</a>.</em></p>\n<h2>God establishes the covenant with Israel on Mount Sinai</h2>\n<h3>Moses performs the ceremony establishing the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4-Exod24:8\">EXO 24:4–24:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Moses and other leaders ascend Mount Sinai to seal the covenant with a meal before God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:9-Exod24:11\">EXO 24:9–24:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Moses ascends Mount Sinai further to receive the stone tablets and the requirements of covenant worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:12-Exod24:18\">EXO 24:12–24:18</a></strong> <em>During Moses' 40 days on Mount Sinai, God revealed to him the requirements of covenant worship, as outlined in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:1-Exod31:18\">Ex 25:1–31:18</a>.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:37-Lev7:38\">LEV 7:37–7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:46\">LEV 26:46</a></p>\n<h2>Moses descends Mount Sinai and discovers Israel's idolatry</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:1-Exod32:6\">EXO 32:1–32:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:21-Exod32:35\">EXO 32:21–32:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:8-Deut9:21\">DEU 9:8–9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:19-Ps106:23\">PSA 106:19–106:23</a></p>\n<h2>God commands Israel to move on from Mount Sinai</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:1-Exod33:6\">EXO 33:1–33:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:15-Exod33:16\">EXO 33:15–33:16</a></p>\n<h2>God calls Moses up Mount Sinai again</h2>\n<h3>Moses is commanded to prepare new stone tablets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1-Exod34:4\">EXO 34:1–34:4</a></p>\n<h3>God reveals his nature and name to Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:5-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:5–34:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God renews his covenant with Israel</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:10-Exod34:28\">EXO 34:10–34:28</a></p>\n<h3>Moses descends Mount Sinai, his face radiant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29-Exod34:35\">EXO 34:29–34:35</a></p>\n<h2>The people of Israel prepare to move on from Mount Sinai</h2>\n<h3>God commands Moses to take a census of Israel in the Desert of Sinai</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:1-Num1:4\">NUM 1:1–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:14-Num3:16\">NUM 3:14–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites celebrate the Passover at Mount Sinai</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:1-Num9:5\">NUM 9:1–9:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites leave Mount Sinai</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:11-Num10:13\">NUM 10:11–10:13</a> <em>The Israelites had been at Mount Sinai for almost a year (see also <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:1\">Ex 19:1</a>)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:6-Deut1:8\">DEU 1:6–1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Later generations look back to God's revelation on Mount Sinai</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:5\">JDG 5:5</a></strong> <em>Ascribing the title “the One of Sinai” to God, Deborah acknowledges the great importance of his revelation at Mount Sinai.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:8-1Kgs19:9\">1KI 19:8–19:9</a> <em>Elijah's return to Horeb, the mountain of God, shows his need to hear God clearly again</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:13-Neh9:14\">NEH 9:13–9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:7-Ps68:8\">PSA 68:7–68:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:19-Ps106:23\">PSA 106:19–106:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:4\">MAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:37-Acts7:38\">ACT 7:37–7:38</a></p>\n<h2>Mount Sinai seen by NT writers as a symbol of the old covenant</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:24-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:24–4:31</a> <em>Hagar, Mount Sinai and the present city of Jerusalem stand for the old covenant and bondage to the law, while Sarah and the new heavenly Jerusalem stand for the new covenant and living by faith</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:18-Heb12:29\">HEB 12:18–12:29</a></p>",
